{"lemma":"نَعْشُ","slug":"نَعْشُ","root":"ن.ع.ش","root_slug":"ن-ع-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ع-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40119"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B4%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"corpse (human)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bier, stretcher","examples":[{"text":"ويقولون للّذي يُحْمَلُ عليه الميّت النَّعَاشُ. والصّواب النَّعْشُ. قال الشّاعر:\nأَمَحْمُولٌ عَلَى النَّعْشِ الهُمَامُ","english":"Them man say for that on which one is carried dead naʕāš. The right is naʕš. A poet (al-Nābiḡa aḏ-Ḏubyāni) said:\nI am carried high on the bier."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lift up, to raise"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to animate, to revive, to restore in health or wealth"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to praise, to eulogize"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lift up, to raise"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to say to someone that he shall rise"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Seemingly a Middle Iranian borrowing equivalent to Persian لاش (lâš). Prefixation to ع ي ش (ʕ y š) as in نَوْرَج (nawraj) is also considered. The verbs in the root ن ع ش (n ʕ š) are denominal in any case."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40119","headword_ar":"نَعْشٌ","root":"nE$","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of elevation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exaltation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh.) See 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of remaining; lastingness; endurance; permanence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaA='N","text_ar":"بَقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sh, K.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of litter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing resembling a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHaf~ap","text_ar":"مِحَفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", upon which the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king used to be carried. when sick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, Msb, K:) not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$","text_ar":"نَعْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a corpse. (IDrd, Msb.) This is said to be the primary application. (TA) ―         -b2-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the corpse is upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"for otherwise it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sriyrN","text_ar":"سرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, IAth, Msb:) it is called by the former name because of its height, or its being raised: (S, TA.) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuEuw$N","text_ar":"نُعُوشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reticulated thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az. Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHaf~p","text_ar":"محَفّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put as a cover over a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dead"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman when she is placed upon the bier;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Mgh, TA;) but this is properly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarajN","text_ar":"حَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though people called is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$N","text_ar":"نَعْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is properly only the bier itself. (Az, TA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu naEo$i AlkuboraY","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ نَعْشِ الكُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$a AlkuboraY","text_ar":"نَعْشَ الكُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$N","text_ar":"نَعْشٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$u","text_ar":"نَعْشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", constitute (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation of Ursa Major:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the principal stars thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven stars; whereof four"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are in the body"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$N","text_ar":"نَعْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$u","text_ar":"نَعْشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and three"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are in the tail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banAtN","text_ar":"بَناتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt nE$","text_ar":"بنات نعش"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to"},{"kind":"text","text":"like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt nE$ AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"بنات نعش الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nE$ AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"نعش الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"constitute ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the constellation of Ursa Minor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the principal stars thereof; seven in number; whereof the four in the body are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nE$","text_ar":"نعش"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the there in the tail are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt","text_ar":"بنات"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) [the former four] said to be likened to the bearers of a bier, because they form a square: (IDrd, TA:) [the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt","text_ar":"بنات"},{"kind":"text","text":"being so called as being likened to damsels or to men for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt","text_ar":"بنات"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to an irrational thing as well as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binotN","text_ar":"بِنْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") following a bier:] Sb and Fr agree that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nE$","text_ar":"نعش"},{"kind":"text","text":"is imperfectly decl. because determinate and of the fem. gender: (S:) or it is perfectly decl. when indeterminate, but not when determinate [by having the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkuboraY","text_ar":"الكُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"added to it]: (Aboo-'Amr Ez-Záhid, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banw naEo$i","text_ar":"بَنو نَعْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs, in poetry; (Sb, S, K;) because a single one [of the stars thereof] is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abonu naEo$i","text_ar":"ابْنُ نَعْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, K,) being made to accord. in gender with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawokabN","text_ar":"كَوْكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but when they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAv","text_ar":"ثَلَاث"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaE","text_ar":"اَرْبَع"},{"kind":"text","text":", they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAt","text_ar":"بَنَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, TA:) [this is agreeable with a general rule; accord. to which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtN","text_ar":"بَنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonN","text_ar":"اِبْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to anything but a human being:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnAt nE$","text_ar":"بنات نعش"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~awaAEi$u","text_ar":"النَّوَاعِشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAriSu","text_ar":"اَبَارِصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm~u A^abaraSa","text_ar":"سَامُّ اَبَرَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuEayo$N","text_ar":"نُعَيْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEo$N","text_ar":"نَعْشٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the length of twice the stature of a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the head of which is a piece of rag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarajN","text_ar":"حَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which young ostriches are hunted"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"captured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IDrd","Msb","K","TA","S","A","IAth","Mgh","Lth"]}]}}